.Ip "\(bu" 2
\f(CW$vector = Bit::Vector->new($bits);\fR
.Sp
This is the bit vector constructor method.
.Sp
Call this method to create a new bit vector containing \*(L"\f(CW$bits\fR\*(R"
bits (with indices ranging from \*(L"\f(CW0\fR\*(R" to \*(L"\f(CW$bits-1\fR").
.Sp
