which happens when the number \*(L"0000...0000\*(R" is decremented,
which gives \*(L"1111...1111\*(R" minus a carry over to the next higher
(binary) digit.
.Sp
This can be used for the terminating condition of a \*(L"while\*(R" loop,
for instance, in order to cycle through all possible values the
bit vector can assume.
.Ip "\(bu" 2
\f(CW$overflow = $vec2->inc($vec1);\fR
.Sp
This method copies the contents of bit vector \*(L"\f(CW$vec1\fR\*(R" to bit
