significant bit is set (i.e., if the bit vector contains a negative
number), or \*(L"\f(CW1\fR\*(R" otherwise (i.e., if the bit vector contains a
positive number).
.Ip "\(bu" 2
\f(CW$vec3->Multiply($vec1,$vec2);\fR
.Sp
This method multiplies the two numbers contained in bit vector \*(L"\f(CW$vec1\fR\*(R"
and \*(L"\f(CW$vec2\fR\*(R" and stores the result in bit vector \*(L"\f(CW$vec3\fR\*(R".
